The paper presents a new nonlinear dimensionality reduction technique for incremental data visualization, which is a common problem in machine learning and artificial intelligence. The paper also compares the proposed technique with other existing techniques such as t-SNE and UMAP, which are commonly used in computer vision and natural language processing. Therefore, the most likely sub-categories are cs.LG (Machine Learning), cs.AI (Artificial Intelligence), and cs.CV (Computer Vision). Additionally, the paper also discusses the algorithmic foundations of the proposed technique, which may fall under cs.NE (Neural and Evolutionary Computing) and cs.SI (Social and Information Networks).
